# Portfolio Redesign Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Redesign the current portfolio website to authentically reflect Liam as a "Jack of all trades" freelancer (Creative Technologist, Designer, Developer). The design should move away from the generic "web developer" tech stack layout. Instead of a sterile or "too cool" aesthetic, the website must retain elements of fun, foolishness, and offbeat style. We will keep the original rainbow flower logo and build a custom, highly interactive canvas that the user can continually fine-tune. We'll also integrate a Spotify player and lay the groundwork for a future blog.

## User Review Required
Please review the proposed design changes below. If you agree with this direction, I will begin execution.
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The current "stack" list heavily emphasizes web dev. I propose we drop tags like "React, Next.js, Rails" in the UI and replace them with broader categories like "Creative Direction, Interaction Design, Software Engineering, Digital Art". This might mean we need to update some content in Sanity CMS later. 
> Also, I plan to remove the smiling rainbow `logo.png` and use a sophisticated typographical wordmark for your identity instead. Are you comfortable with this?

## Proposed Changes

### Core Aesthetics & Branding
- **Vibe & Style**: Offbeat, fun, authentic, and slightly foolish. Not a generic, polished corporate site. We want custom cursor interactions, surprising hover states, or unconventional layouts.
- **Typography**: We'll introduce some interesting typefaces for headers but allow for fine-tune control so the user can continually tweak the font pairings.
- **Color Palette**: We will experiment with color, potentially contrasting the dark background with vibrant, unexpected pops of color that complement the rainbow logo.
- **Identity (Logo)**: Retain the `logo.png` (the smiling rainbow flower) as a core anchor to the fun and authentic identity.

---

### Layout & Components
#### [MODIFY] [src/app/page.tsx](file:///Users/stricko/code/str1ck0/portfolio/src/app/page.tsx)
- Remove the rigid 240px grid-lined sidebar wrapper.
- Change the layout to an immersive, full-screen canvas. The navigation will become a sleek floating element or a highly spaced, minimal header, allowing the gallery of work to take center stage.
- Update the layout structure to allow content to flow more organically rather than in constrained boxes.

#### [MODIFY] [src/components/CollapsibleMenu.tsx](file:///Users/stricko/code/str1ck0/portfolio/src/components/CollapsibleMenu.tsx) & [src/components/AboutText.tsx](file:///Users/stricko/code/str1ck0/portfolio/src/components/AboutText.tsx)
- Refactor the "Stack" section. Instead of a tech stack list, we will label this "Disciplines" or "Practice" and focus on broader creative technology skills.
- Add an embedded Spotify Player component to the sidebar or menu.
- Redesign the menu to feel less like a dense dashboard and more like an interactive, experimental navigation.

#### [NEW] `src/components/SpotifyPlayer.tsx`
- Create a new component to house a Spotify iframe element, allowing a site playlist to be permanently playable.

#### [MODIFY] [src/components/Background.tsx](file:///Users/stricko/code/str1ck0/portfolio/src/components/Background.tsx)
- Create an offbeat background effect—perhaps something interactive, retro, or slightly erratic that captures the "foolish/fun" aesthetic.

#### [MODIFY] [src/components/Gallery.tsx](file:///Users/stricko/code/str1ck0/portfolio/src/components/Gallery.tsx) & [src/components/ProjectDetail.tsx](file:///Users/stricko/code/str1ck0/portfolio/src/components/ProjectDetail.tsx)
- Remove the literal mobile phone mockup framing unless absolutely necessary.
- Display projects as large, high-res edge-to-edge images or in an editorial masonry grid with smooth parity transitions.
- Enhance the interaction with smooth hover states, cursor-following elements, and elegant crossfades when opening a project detail view.

---

### Interactions
#### [MODIFY] [package.json](file:///Users/stricko/code/str1ck0/portfolio/package.json)
- Install `framer-motion` to handle high-end micro-interactions, page transitions (like the `AnimatePresence` idea discussed previously), and smooth scrolling.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run lint` and `npm run build` to ensure no build errors are introduced.

### Manual Verification
- View the site on `localhost:3000` via the browser subagent and verify the layout feels premium and responsive.
- Verify that the dark mode aesthetics, typography, and new abstract wordmark render correctly without the old playful elements.
- Ensure the project gallery opens smoothly without phone mockup constraints.
